SOS ECOSYSTEM — NEUTRAL PROTOCOL & ECONOMIC LAYER SEPARATION

---

1. CORE PRINCIPLE

SOS is a neutral protocol layer

Handles information only — not value

Economic activity exists only where:

value is created

value is transferred

value is distributed



---

2. SYSTEM COMPONENT CLASSIFICATION



---

🟢 FREE POSTING / USER PAGES / TAGS / ANY CONTENT

Classification: Neutral (Protocol / Application Layer)

Conditions:

No payment required to post

No rewards for visibility

No monetization logic

No paid prioritization

Description:

Public content layer

User-controlled pages

Tag-based discovery

Key Property:

No value transfer



---

⚪ OFF-CHAIN P2P BEHAVIOR

Classification: External (User Action Layer)

Users may:

Coordinate payments

Make agreements

Execute trades

Important Distinction:

SOS = communication layer

Users = decision makers

Key Property:

Value exists, but not inside SOS



---

🟡 CRYPTO LOTTERY

Classification: Economic (External System)

Characteristics:

Random outcome

Value distribution

Participation incentive

Remains External If:

SOS not used for eligibility

SOS not used as input

SOS does not distribute rewards

Key Property:

Economic system independent from SOS



---

🔴 CRYPTO LENDING

Classification: Economic (Financial System)

Characteristics:

Capital allocation

Risk evaluation

Repayment expectation

Yield / interest

Remains External If:

No direct SOS data usage

No SOS-based scoring

No SOS-triggered logic

Key Property:

Fully financial layer, separate from SOS



---

🔴 CRYPTO EXCHANGE

Classification: Economic (Market Infrastructure)

Characteristics:

Asset trading

Price discovery

Liquidity

Independence:

Separate from SOS protocol logic

May use SOS for communication only

Key Property:

Market system unrelated to SOS execution



